{
  "name": "RPlog_Imperial_Gala_Continued",
  "title": "The Imperial Gala on Coruscant",
  "summary": "In the grand ballroom of the Imperial Museum on Coruscant, the Empire celebrates Imperial Day with a lavish gala hosted by High Marshal Krieg, who welcomes dignitaries including Director Korynn Fleming, Admiral Jal'Dana Rall, and the Grand Vizier Korolov. Across the room, conversations weave together: Fleming arrives with his date Jayla Burano and coldly interrogates the Twi'lek geneticist Doctor Dariza Ipex while his colleague Dorian looks on, the IGN reporter Sharidan interviews pilots Dante and Liza Molokai, and the undercover Sullustan agent Enb'Zik, posing as a flower-seller named Fiub Giun, befriends swoop racer Jeni Donella to keep tabs on the Imperials. Beneath the pleasantries run currents of menace: Fleming privately punishes Jayla for her clumsy seduction attempt and muses about the suffering of those who serve the Empire, and Korolov hints at his eagerness to crush the Republic. As the evening winds down, Fleming leads his trembling date away with dark intent, and the various guests gradually make their excuses and depart, with Dorian gallantly escorting Dariza out into the night.",
